placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.dialogId=The dialog ID to use for the dialogue. Leave empty to make no bubble appear.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.flipY=Flips the sprite of the NPC vertically.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.flipX=Flips the sprite of the NPC horizontally.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.onlyOnce=Whether the dialogue should only be completable once.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.endLevel=Whether finishing the dialogue should count as completing the map.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.approachWhenTalking=Whether Madeline should walk towards the NPC when talking.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.approachDistance=How far away from the NPC Madeline should stop when approaching.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.spriteName=The name of the animation to use, from your map's Sprites.xml or from the vanilla one.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.onlyIfFlag=If set, the player will only be able to talk to the NPC when the given flag is active.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.setFlag=If set, the given flag will be activated once the player is done talking to the NPC.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/CustomNPCSprite.tooltips.autoSkipEnabled=Checking this allows you to enable dialogue auto-skipping by using {trigger 0}, and to disable it with {trigger 1}.\nThese triggers have to be used within the dialogue text, in English.txt.

