placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/MadelineSprite.tooltips.hasBackpack=Whether the Madeline sprite should have a backpack.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/MadelineSprite.tooltips.left=Whether the Madeline sprite should face left.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/MadelineSprite.tooltips.dashCount=The dash count Madeline has. Determines Madeline's hair color.

# Spinner Breaking Ball
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SpinnerBreakingBall.tooltips.color=The color of the spinners this ball is able to break.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SpinnerBreakingBall.tooltips.spritePath=The sprite this ball should use, from your mod's Graphics/Atlases/Gameplay folder.\nContributions for proper default sprites are welcome.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SpinnerBreakingBall.tooltips.startFloating=Whether the ball should float in mid-air until the player picks it up.

# Styleground Fade Controller
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/StylegroundFadeController.names.flag=Flags
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/StylegroundFadeController.tooltips.flag=This controller will affect the stylegrounds that have one of these flags in their "Flag" field.\nThe stylegrounds should be toggled by one flag only, not with room names for example.\nIf you specify multiple flags separated by commas, it will work the same as placing multiple controllers with one flag each.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/StylegroundFadeController.tooltips.fadeInTime=The time it will take for the stylegrounds to fully fade in, in seconds. Vanilla value is 1 second.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/StylegroundFadeController.tooltips.fadeOutTime=The time it will take for the stylegrounds to fully fade out, in seconds. Vanilla stylegrounds don't fade out.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/StylegroundFadeController.tooltips.notFlag=Whether this controller will affect the stylegrounds that have the given flags in their "Not Flag" field, instead of their "Flag" field.

# Reskinnable Crystal Heart
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.fake=Whether the heart is fake and should visually be grey. Triggers the Farewell fake heart cutscene.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.removeCameraTriggers=Whether the heart should remove camera triggers onces its triggered. Only usable if fake attribute is set.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.fakeHeartDialog=Initial dialogue for the fake heart.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.keepGoingDialog=Dialogue after the fake heart shatters.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.sprite=The sprite ID from Sprites.xml to use when the heart was not collected on this save file yet (or all the time if "Disable Ghost Sprite" is enabled).\nLeave blank to use the default sprite.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.ghostSprite=The sprite ID from Sprites.xml to use when the heart is already collected.\nLeave blank to use the default sprite.\nUnused when "Disable Ghost Sprite" is enabled.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.particleColor=The color of the particles that the heart emits.\nLeave blank to use the default color.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.flagOnCollect=The session flag to set when the heart is collected.\nLeave blank if you do not want any flag to be set.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.flagInverted=If enabled, the flag specified in "Flag On Collect" will be disabled when the heart is collected, instead of being enabled.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/ReskinnableCrystalHeart.tooltips.disableGhostSprite=If this option is enabled, the heart will look the same no matter if it was already collected or not, and will never use its ghost sprite.

# Set Flag on Button Press Controller
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnButtonPressController.tooltips.button=The button this controller should react to.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnButtonPressController.tooltips.flag=The flag that should be set whenever the button is held.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnButtonPressController.tooltips.inverted=If checked, the flag will be disabled rather than enabled when the button is held.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnButtonPressController.tooltips.toggleMode=If checked, the flag will be toggled each time the button is pressed, instead of being enabled whenever the button is held.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnButtonPressController.tooltips.activationDelay=The time (in seconds) the button has to be held before the flag is activated or toggled.

