placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnActionController.tooltips.action=The player action this controller should react to.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnActionController.tooltips.flag=The flag that should be set whenever the player is doing the action.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SetFlagOnActionController.tooltips.inverted=If checked, the flag will be disabled rather than enabled when the player is doing the action.

# Flag Pickup
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagPickup.tooltips.appearOnFlag=If specified, the pickup will only appear when the given flag is active.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagPickup.tooltips.flagOnPickup=If specified, the pickup will activate the given flag when collected.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagPickup.tooltips.collectFlag=If specified, the pickup will follow the player and only collect when the specified flag is activated.\nIf not specified, the pickup will be collected immediately when picked up.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagPickup.tooltips.spriteName=The sprite to use for the pickup.\nYou can make your own by copying "MaxHelpingHand_FlagPickup_Flag" from Graphics/Sprites.xml in Helping Hand's zip,\nand pasting it in your map's Sprites.xml in order to customize it.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagPickup.tooltips.collectSound=The sound that plays when the pickup is collected.\nLeave this field empty for no sound.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagPickup.tooltips.allowRespawn=Whether the flag pickup should respawn after being picked up and dying / changing rooms.\nWarning: this can cause multiple instances of the pickup to coexist if you have defined a "Collect Flag".

# Flag Decal
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.names.fps=Frame Rate (FPS)
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.tooltips.fps=The speed of the animations, in frames per second.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.tooltips.flag=The flag this decal should react to.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.tooltips.inverted=If enabled, the decal will appear when the flag is inactive, rather than when it is active.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.tooltips.decalPath=The path to the decal, starting from Graphics/Atlases/Gameplay/decals in the graphics dump or in your mod's folder.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.tooltips.appearAnimationPath=The path to an appearing animation for the decal, starting from Graphics/Atlases/Gameplay/decals in the graphics dump or in your mod's folder.\nIf none is specified, the decal will appear immediately.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.tooltips.disappearAnimationPath=The path to a disappearing animation for the decal, starting from Graphics/Atlases/Gameplay/decals in the graphics dump or in your mod's folder.\nIf none is specified, the decal will disappear immediately.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/FlagDecal.tooltips.depth=The depth of the decal, relative to other decals. You can input a number if you want a custom depth.

# Save File Strawberry Gate
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SaveFileStrawberryGate.tooltips.requires=Determines the number of strawberries required to open the gate.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SaveFileStrawberryGate.tooltips.startHidden=Whether the door should start hidden and come crashing down when the player approaches.\nWill destroy dash blocks as it crashes down.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SaveFileStrawberryGate.tooltips.freeze=Whether the opening animation should include time freezes.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SaveFileStrawberryGate.tooltips.shake=Whether the opening animation should include screen shake.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SaveFileStrawberryGate.tooltips.countFrom=Determines which strawberries are taken into account to unlock the gate.\nIf you want to only take strawberries collected during the current session into account, use a regular Strawberry Gate from Lunatic Helper instead.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SaveFileStrawberryGate.tooltips.persistent=Whether the strawberry gate should stay open having been opened for the first time, even if the player exits the map and enters it again.
placements.entities.MaxHelpingHand/SaveFileStrawberryGate.tooltips.showCounter=If enabled, a strawberry counter will appear on the gate instead of the berry icons.\nThis can be useful if the amount of strawberries required does not fit on the screen.

